{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17503763","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17503763"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:06:47+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:06:47+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2076"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2076","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2076"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.13,0.26,0.17,0.39]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2076"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"31539"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2076","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2076"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2076"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"17328"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"687"},{"type":"tags","id":"3049"},{"type":"tags","id":"4952"},{"type":"tags","id":"4971"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11624"},{"type":"tags","id":"11632"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"129"},{"type":"contributions","id":"144"},{"type":"contributions","id":"268"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42455"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"31539","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/31539"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 20-year-old man was found unconscious at home. He was intubated at the scene and brought to the Emergency Department. Collateral history from his girlfriend suggests that he had deliberately overdosed on an unknown number of amitriptyline tablets 1 hour ago. He suffers from depression but has no other medical history. He takes no other medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn clinical review, he remains unconscious and ventilated via an endotracheal tube. He is saturating at 98%. His pulse rate is 120/min and blood pressure 116/82mmHg. His ECG shows a sinus tachycardia with a QRS duration of 180ms and prolongation of the QT interval. There were no significant findings on cardiorespiratory examination.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["DC cardioversion","IV amiodarone","IV calcium gluconate","IV magnesium sulfate","IV sodium bicarbonate"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient\u0027s ECG findings are typical of tricyclic antidepressant (TCA) overdose. A QRS of \u0026gt;160ms is associated with a ~50% risk of developing a ventricular arrhythmia and a significantly increased risk of seizures. IV \u003Cstrong\u003Esodium bicarbonate\u003C/strong\u003E is cardioprotective and can narrow the QRS complex in these patients. It is therefore the first-line treatment of QRS widening due to TCA overdose.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDC cardioversion is inappropriate at this stage. Despite the QRS and QT changes, the patient is in sinus tachycardia, so would not benefit from DC cardioversion. If the patient had developed a ventricular arrhythmia, DC cardioversion would be warranted.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAmiodarone, an anti-arrhythmic, is contraindicated in TCA overdose due to its effect of prolonging the QT interval, which can increase the risk of developing a ventricular tachycardia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECalcium gluconate is used in hyperkalaemia to stabilise the cardiac membrane and lower the risk of developing a fatal arrhythmia. Its use has not been validated in the setting of TCA overdose.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMagnesium sulfate can be used as an adjunct treatment in TCA overdose if the QRS changes are refractory to initial bicarbonate treatment. However, it is not a first-line treatment.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["An overdose with a tricyclic carries a significant risk of a potentially fatal ventricular arrhythmia."],"references":["Kerr GW, McGuffie AC, Wilkie S. Tricyclic antidepressant overdose: a review. Emerg Med J. 2001 Jul;18(4):236-41. doi: 10.1136/emj.18.4.236. PMID: 11435353; PMCID: PMC1725608."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"17328"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2076"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"17328","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/17328"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-01-12T13:53:47+10:30","updatedAt":"2023-01-12T13:53:47+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2076"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"31539"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a gra